snippet.textDisplay:
This event is far the most profitable one ubisoft has made for their playerbase. It not only fits the narrative of the game, but also the Esports aspect of the game with the invitational skins. Money is donated towards the Funding of its Esports, newcomers get to play an easy map with all the operators for free, and there is consumer friendly monetization included in the battle pass (no paywall for buying skin lootboxes anymore; a cheaper price to grind for content).
The only thing I'm upset about is the year 5 season pass, because its not coming out with 8 operators, so I expect a cheaper price (but this could imply more engine improvements like operation health did and could fix floating debris for example).
This is far better than CSGO, Apex Legends and Overwatch in terms of gameplay and monetization. This is a good step in the right direction for Ubisoft.
